02:19:25.140 --> 02:19:29.555
TRAVIS: Nice. Slick.

02:19:29.555 --> 02:19:33.202
MATT: "So what can I get you? I've got all sorts
of salves and spices. We've got all sorts of

02:19:33.266 --> 02:19:35.793
"incense. What are you looking for?"

02:19:35.793 --> 02:19:40.297
TRAVIS: Inside the shop, has it grown or become
more ornate since we've last been here?

02:19:40.297 --> 02:19:44.283
MATT: It does, actually. Last time you were here
it was in the process of being put together. The

02:19:44.283 --> 02:19:50.448
shop seems to be fully open now and outfitted,
though it doesn't seem to be getting much traffic,

02:19:50.448 --> 02:19:59.506
as it is very empy. So he seems eager he has
customers. And now much more put at ease, now that

02:19:59.570 --> 02:20:04.902
you've let him know that from his vision, the
dragon woman did not come with you.

02:20:04.902 --> 02:20:10.542
TRAVIS: Yeah. (laughs) You first.

02:20:10.542 --> 02:20:19.532
SAM: Oh, for myself, do you have any spell
scrolls, or any sort of one-use items that I could

02:20:19.532 --> 02:20:27.465
use in a fight or a tangle with some bad chaps?

02:20:27.465 --> 02:20:31.441
MATT: "Let me see what I've got."

02:20:31.441 --> 02:20:35.743
SAM: Things that could deceive, things that could
use force against--

02:20:35.743 --> 02:20:48.773
MATT: And he rummages through a couple of scroll
pieces. Let's see here what he might have. "I do,

02:20:48.773 --> 02:20:58.652
"should you be so interested, currently carry one
scroll that would surround with you a wreath of

02:20:58.652 --> 02:21:00.645
"dangerous fire."

02:21:00.645 --> 02:21:06.760
SAM: Oh, all right. Just around me, or around an
area?

02:21:06.760 --> 02:21:11.698
MATT: "Just around you. Anything that came too
close would burst into flames and be burned."

02:21:11.698 --> 02:21:17.877
SAM: I have 13 of those right here. Do you have
anything else?

02:21:21.529 --> 02:21:22.983
TRAVIS: Not that that's not really impressive.

02:21:23.033 --> 02:21:24.428
SAM: It's really good.

02:21:24.428 --> 02:21:26.786
MATT: "I've got something that makes you jump."

02:21:26.786 --> 02:21:28.773
SAM: I've got that.

02:21:28.773 --> 02:21:30.838
MATT: "I've got something that makes you see in
the dark."

02:21:30.838 --> 02:21:32.956
SAM: Yeah, I have a light already.

02:21:32.956 --> 02:21:36.950
(all laugh)

02:21:36.950 --> 02:21:40.060
MATT: "What do you want?"

02:21:40.060 --> 02:21:45.180
SAM: All right, give me that one scroll, the fire
scroll. I could sell it and get something else.

02:21:45.180 --> 02:21:47.697
MATT: "All right."

02:21:47.697 --> 02:21:49.323
SAM: How much is that?

02:21:49.323 --> 02:21:52.911
MATT: I'm looking right now for the scroll that's
here.

02:21:52.911 --> 02:21:55.298
TRAVIS: You have to read the scroll, right?

02:21:55.298 --> 02:22:03.322
SAM: I could read it to you. If that's what you're
asking.

02:22:03.322 --> 02:22:10.490
MATT: He looks you over. "The scroll I would put
at a fair 6,000 gold pieces."

02:22:10.490 --> 02:22:19.745
SAM: (gulps) Watch how it's done. I'm going to put
an amount of gold on the table. I'd like you to

02:22:19.745 --> 02:22:29.609
consider it, and if it's to your liking, take it,
and if not, just shake your head. And I'll put 200

02:22:29.609 --> 02:22:56.710
gold on the table. I'll put 200 more. I'll put
2,000 more. And another 2,000.

02:22:56.710 --> 02:22:59.082
MATT: Make a persuasion check.

02:22:59.082 --> 02:23:00.591
TRAVIS: 4,400.

02:23:00.591 --> 02:23:04.624
SAM: 17. Plus seven! 24.

02:23:07.905 --> 02:23:10.621
MATT: Takes the gold.

02:23:10.621 --> 02:23:13.022
TRAVIS: Wow!

02:23:13.022 --> 02:23:15.330
SAM: Check and mate.

02:23:15.330 --> 02:23:17.526
TRAVIS: Check'n'mate?

02:23:17.526 --> 02:23:19.310
MATT: You now have a scroll of fire shield.

02:23:19.310 --> 02:23:24.432
SAM: Scroll of fire shield, excellent. I don't
know what that is.

02:23:24.432 --> 02:23:30.034
TRAVIS: Wow. Do you have anything that makes you
faster?

02:23:30.034 --> 02:23:32.361
MATT: "I said I have something that makes you
jump."

02:23:32.361 --> 02:23:40.778
TRAVIS: No. I'm pretty good at jumping. What about
regular healing potions?

02:23:40.778 --> 02:23:47.051
MATT: "That I've got! You cleared me out of my
other various vials last time."

02:23:47.102 --> 02:23:49.201
TRAVIS: No new exotics came in?

02:23:49.201 --> 02:23:54.285
MATT: "No, I'm waiting on-- Trade's been a little
slow. Looks like things are getting up in Emon, so

02:23:54.285 --> 02:23:58.781
"hopefully we'll have more soon. But for the time
being, I do have some more healing potions." And

02:23:58.781 --> 02:24:02.404
he goes into the back room, and you hear him
rummaging for a minute. You hear one crate fall

02:24:02.404 --> 02:24:06.483
over and a couple of things shatter. "Ah god
damn--". And eventually he comes back through the

02:24:06.483 --> 02:24:11.295
door, and he's holding in his arms a few clusters
of various glass vials. Some of them have been

02:24:11.295 --> 02:24:16.506
repurposed and taped at the top, but they're
functional. He sets them down on the counter. "All

02:24:16.506 --> 02:24:31.219
"right. I have six potions of healing, and I have
three of greater healing, and one superior."

02:24:31.219 --> 02:24:33.827
SAM: Do I know how much these things tend to
cost?

02:24:33.827 --> 02:24:36.374
MATT: Make an intelligence check.

02:24:36.374 --> 02:24:41.408
SAM: Ooh! This is not a save.

02:24:41.408 --> 02:24:45.373
MATT: Yes, just add your modifier.

02:24:45.891 --> 02:24:47.891
SAM: 20!

02:24:47.891 --> 02:24:55.420
MATT: Yes, actually. The healing potions
can range around 75 to 100 gold pieces generally.

02:24:55.630 --> 02:25:06.434
The uncommon ones can range somewhere in the 500
gold pieces range. The superior, however, are much

02:25:06.434 --> 02:25:11.583
rarer to come by, and the fact he even has one,
with how recently you guys cleared him out, it's

02:25:11.583 --> 02:25:16.631
pretty decent. That one can run anywhere between
4,000-5,000 gold pieces.

02:25:16.631 --> 02:25:19.324
SAM: And it's six, three, and one? Is that right?

02:25:19.324 --> 02:25:22.240
MATT: Six, three, and one.

02:25:22.698 --> 02:25:26.476
TRAVIS: Do you want to get them? It seems like you
got all the money in the world.

02:25:26.476 --> 02:25:31.734
SAM: I can heal myself just fine, but I don't know
about your friends--

02:25:31.734 --> 02:25:34.954
do they have healing abilities?

02:25:34.954 --> 02:25:39.292
TRAVIS: No, not-- well they do, they touch you
with their hand and then like all of a sudden it

02:25:39.292 --> 02:25:40.821
feels a bit better.

02:25:40.821 --> 02:25:41.791
SAM: A bit better?

02:25:41.791 --> 02:25:43.323
TRAVIS: Yeah. I don't really know how that works.

02:25:43.323 --> 02:25:45.548
SAM: But they use potions. I've seen them use
potions.

02:25:45.548 --> 02:25:48.354
TRAVIS: Yeah, I'm normally pouring them in their
mouths.

02:25:48.919 --> 02:25:52.380
SAM: Do you think they would appreciate these?

02:25:52.380 --> 02:26:01.274
TRAVIS: I don't know, I hadn't thought that far.
As a (mumbling) new member of Vox Machina--

02:26:01.274 --> 02:26:02.860
SAM: What was that?

02:26:02.860 --> 02:26:07.542
TRAVIS: Bad allergies here. It could be like a
really great gift, you know?

02:26:07.542 --> 02:26:10.379
Like Keyleth gave you.

02:26:10.379 --> 02:26:12.109
SAM: -- welcome-me-to-the-gang gift.

02:26:12.109 --> 02:26:14.001
TRAVIS: Yeah.

02:26:14.001 --> 02:26:17.864
SAM: Do you gift-wrap, here, sir?

02:26:17.864 --> 02:26:22.689
MATT: "For an additional charge, yes, of course, I
gift wrap!"

02:26:22.689 --> 02:26:30.455
SAM: -- of course for an additional charge. What
if we took the whole lot of those for 6,000 gold?

02:26:31.760 --> 02:26:38.027
MATT: "The whole lot? For 6,000. I'm afraid that
is far under the price I'd be considering. Let me

02:26:38.027 --> 02:26:47.222
"see here." And he does some kind of notations, and
he goes, "Hm. You seem, from our previous

02:26:47.222 --> 02:26:52.521
"experience, to be quite the bargainer, my
friend."

02:26:52.521 --> 02:26:54.419
TRAVIS: Yeah, the brains.

02:26:54.419 --> 02:27:00.202
MATT: "How would you say to the fair price of
10,000 gold pieces for the batch?"

02:27:02.263 --> 02:27:09.721
TRAVIS: Let me confer with my partner. (whispers)
How many on your hands is that? Yeah, no-- both

02:27:09.721 --> 02:27:11.334
hands, how many?

02:27:11.334 --> 02:27:12.520
SAM: All.

02:27:12.520 --> 02:27:13.612
TRAVIS: Two?

02:27:13.612 --> 02:27:15.075
SAM: Oh. Wait.

02:27:15.075 --> 02:27:18.714
(all laugh)

02:27:18.714 --> 02:27:20.016
SAM: It's too much.

02:27:20.016 --> 02:27:21.199
TRAVIS: Too much.

02:27:21.199 --> 02:27:26.889
SAM: Yes. This man is insulting your intelligence,
and you should be very angry right now.

02:27:28.847 --> 02:27:43.574
TRAVIS: How about 9,000 gold pieces?

02:27:43.574 --> 02:27:53.484
MATT: "Mm, you drive a very hard bargain, my big
friend, however! Because it's you? Deal."

02:27:53.484 --> 02:27:55.132
TRAVIS: Done! Pay the man.

02:27:55.132 --> 02:28:03.431
SAM: I would object to this. This is coming out of
my purse, and I insist that you negotiate with me,

02:28:03.431 --> 02:28:06.277
and not--

02:28:06.277 --> 02:28:11.849
TRAVIS: Tary, this man drives a really well-known
establishment. If we leave here, after having

02:28:11.849 --> 02:28:17.563
struck that bargain, and we don't pay? There will
be more guards outside.

02:28:17.563 --> 02:28:27.479
SAM: (gulps) How about this. I can trade you
something worth far more than the extra 3,000 gold

02:28:27.479 --> 02:28:31.210
this gentleman promised you.

02:28:31.210 --> 02:28:34.702
MATT: "What would this be?"

02:28:34.702 --> 02:28:49.834
SAM: It's a rare egg. Magical in nature. It can
save a life, in any situation. And if you eat it

02:28:49.834 --> 02:28:58.129
when you are nearly dead, you will go back into
battle with the strength and bravery of ten men,

02:28:58.129 --> 02:29:02.156
and you will not rest until your foes are dead.

02:29:03.722 --> 02:29:07.245
MATT: Make a persuasion check. This isn't
deception because you believe this

02:29:07.245 --> 02:29:08.912
wholeheartedly.

02:29:08.912 --> 02:29:13.026
SAM: Is this deception or persuasion?

02:29:13.026 --> 02:29:14.525
MATT: This is persuasion.

02:29:14.525 --> 02:29:16.142
SAM: 22.

02:29:25.297 --> 02:29:36.237
MATT: "6,000 and the egg, you say? Very well." He
pushes the--

02:29:36.237 --> 02:29:37.776
SAM: Gentle!

02:29:37.776 --> 02:29:48.750
MATT: "I will be." He goes over and quickly
reaches over and grabs a thick towel-like pile of

02:29:48.750 --> 02:29:57.256
cloth, and wraps it up carefully. "Ooh." Sets it
down. "A pleasure doing business with you all."

02:29:57.256 --> 02:30:00.640
SAM: Ah-ah-ah. The gift-wrapping?

02:30:00.640 --> 02:30:03.645
(all laugh)

02:30:03.697 --> 02:30:10.087
MATT: "Terribly sorry. My apologies. I'll be right
to it." And he turns and leaves the room.

02:30:10.087 --> 02:30:14.921
TRAVIS: Tary, that was a personal gift from me to
you.

02:30:15.604 --> 02:30:22.496
SAM: I know, but we're partners, as you just said,
and I felt that you would approve of me doing so.

02:30:23.113 --> 02:30:26.690
TRAVIS: I suppose I am a bit proud.

02:30:27.707 --> 02:30:29.613
MATT: (loud clanging)

02:30:29.613 --> 02:30:30.734
SAM: What was that?

02:30:30.734 --> 02:30:32.075
MATT: You hear behind you guys in the doorway--

02:30:32.075 --> 02:30:33.066
SAM: Oh shit. Oh shit.

02:30:33.066 --> 02:30:35.936
MATT: -- some of the impacts of metal, rapidly and
heavily.

02:30:35.936 --> 02:30:37.549
TRAVIS: What?

02:30:37.549 --> 02:30:38.458
SAM: Sword!

02:30:38.458 --> 02:30:39.664
TRAVIS: Oh Jesus.

02:30:39.664 --> 02:30:46.585
MATT: You watch, (whoosh), whips into a longsword.
And you glance behind and you see, walking through

02:30:46.585 --> 02:30:51.753
the doorway, the very heavy, hulking figure of
Doty, carrying two unconscious guards that are

02:30:51.753 --> 02:30:53.387
hanging from his hands.

02:30:53.387 --> 02:30:55.589
SAM: Oh shit.

02:30:55.589 --> 02:31:04.486
TRAVIS: What did you do? Give me those! I punch
them both, one time each, in the jaw, just for

02:31:04.486 --> 02:31:06.718
extra measure.

02:31:07.818 --> 02:31:12.376
MATT: Okay. Both jaws are very broken.

02:31:13.210 --> 02:31:16.841
TRAVIS: Your guy really did a number. Cool. Okay.

02:31:16.841 --> 02:31:19.952
(all laugh)

02:31:19.952 --> 02:31:23.538
TRAVIS: Everybody's going to die, all right? So
we're going to kill everyone that we see in the

02:31:23.538 --> 02:31:24.565
next ten seconds.

02:31:24.565 --> 02:31:25.956
SAM: Wait, we're killing them? Even the shop
owner?

02:31:25.956 --> 02:31:27.270
TRAVIS: Yeah, he's got to die.

02:31:27.270 --> 02:31:31.820
SAM: Oh shit. All right. Partners, right? I'll do
whatever you say.

02:31:31.820 --> 02:31:33.848
TRAVIS: Is there a counter in the shop?

02:31:33.848 --> 02:31:35.950
MATT: Yeah, there's a counter in the front area.

02:31:35.950 --> 02:31:37.199
TRAVIS: Is it wooden?

02:31:37.199 --> 02:31:38.090
MATT: Yeah.

02:31:38.090 --> 02:31:39.142
TRAVIS: Can he see through the counter?

02:31:39.142 --> 02:31:42.131
MATT: No, the proprietor is in the back room. He's
wrapping your stuff right now.

02:31:42.131 --> 02:31:45.167
SAM: He doesn't know this happened. Let's get rid
of them. Get rid of them.

02:31:45.167 --> 02:31:49.067
TRAVIS: Well, what's in the shop? Is there a
tapestry, is there a rug?

02:31:49.067 --> 02:31:52.126
MATT: It's not a very big-- There is a secondary
room to the side where it looks like there is an

02:31:52.126 --> 02:31:54.889
upper platform, but that looks like where his
bedroom is, maybe.

02:31:54.889 --> 02:31:56.019
TRAVIS: Uh-huh.

02:31:56.019 --> 02:31:58.668
MATT: There's a couple of lanterns, it's a
warm-lit interior, and as you're looking around,

02:31:58.668 --> 02:32:03.243
it's not a huge establishment. Make a perception
check.

02:32:05.908 --> 02:32:07.567
TRAVIS: Yeah. Two.

02:32:07.567 --> 02:32:09.422
MATT: You have no idea! You're panicking.

02:32:09.422 --> 02:32:12.762
TRAVIS: I saw this in a tavern once. Let's sit
them up like they're just sleeping

02:32:12.762 --> 02:32:15.537
and nobody will notice.

02:32:15.537 --> 02:32:20.043
SAM: They have jaws-- the blood! Their jaws are
terrible!

02:32:20.043 --> 02:32:23.020
TRAVIS: Well, didn't you put a mask on Dotty?
Let's do it again.

02:32:23.020 --> 02:32:25.010
SAM: I can't! I don't have extra masks.

02:32:25.010 --> 02:32:26.407
TRAVIS: No, it will be no problem.

02:32:26.407 --> 02:32:28.416
SAM: We can put them somewhere else.

02:32:28.416 --> 02:32:32.355
TRAVIS: I sit one up in the corner, and I sit the
other one, and lean it on his shoulder.

02:32:32.355 --> 02:32:34.645
MATT: Okay.

02:32:34.934 --> 02:32:37.900
SAM: Oh my god. What?

02:32:37.900 --> 02:32:39.305
TRAVIS: This is great. Don't worry.

02:32:39.305 --> 02:32:41.837
SAM: Even I can tell that those are two--

02:32:41.837 --> 02:32:44.897
TRAVIS: I have an even better idea! I take the
cask of ale out of the bag of holding, and I just

02:32:44.897 --> 02:32:47.614
start pouring ale all over them.

02:32:47.614 --> 02:32:50.045
SAM: Why would they be in here drinking? They're
guards on duty!

02:32:50.045 --> 02:32:53.589
TRAVIS: They're terrible guards. They make
horrible life choices. They're in the wrong line

02:32:53.589 --> 02:32:58.944
of work. I take two chalices and I throw it in
their laps. Cool.

02:32:58.944 --> 02:33:01.054
Now I need you to vomit on them.

02:33:01.054 --> 02:33:03.258
SAM: I can't vomit.

02:33:03.258 --> 02:33:06.675
TRAVIS: Do it right now. Put your finger down your
throat and puke on these guards.

02:33:06.675 --> 02:33:09.171
MATT: Make an intimidation check, Grog.

02:33:11.167 --> 02:33:14.002
TRAVIS: 17! Puke on those fucking guards!

02:33:14.002 --> 02:33:14.919
SAM: What do I roll?

02:33:14.919 --> 02:33:19.376
MATT: I'm going to say, make an insight check.
Sure.

02:33:19.376 --> 02:33:21.166
SAM: 16.

02:33:21.166 --> 02:33:26.208
TRAVIS: Vomit on those bitches.

02:33:26.208 --> 02:33:31.375
SAM: (dry heaving)

02:33:31.375 --> 02:33:33.337
MATT: And that's going to be giffed forever.

02:33:33.337 --> 02:33:39.224
(all laugh)

02:33:39.224 --> 02:33:43.485
MATT: Make a constitution saving throw.

02:33:43.485 --> 02:33:46.168
SAM: Natural 20.

02:33:46.168 --> 02:33:52.960
MATT: About 30 seconds of you trying to gag
yourself pass, before the shop owner comes back,

02:33:52.960 --> 02:33:58.427
with these beautifully packaged healing potions.
"All right, so--"

02:33:58.427 --> 02:34:01.324
SAM: One second! One second.

02:34:01.324 --> 02:34:06.551
TRAVIS: I'm really sorry. These two gentlemen
obviously have been off their ass. They came in

02:34:06.551 --> 02:34:11.813
here, smelling of booze, looking for something to
make them feel better, I don't know, and they just

02:34:11.813 --> 02:34:15.934
passed out in the corner. Is there someone you
know that we can call? I really hate just leaving

02:34:15.934 --> 02:34:17.067
them here.

02:34:17.067 --> 02:34:18.578
MATT: Make a deception check.

02:34:18.578 --> 02:34:21.430
MARISHA: Oh my god. Come on, Grog!

02:34:21.430 --> 02:34:22.532
TALIESIN: Please a four.

02:34:22.532 --> 02:34:23.680
TRAVIS: Nine.

02:34:23.680 --> 02:34:25.060
TALIESIN: Yes!

02:34:25.060 --> 02:34:32.192
MATT: He slowly hands out this really nice bundle,
and it has a little bow on it and it's wrapped,

02:34:32.192 --> 02:34:41.796
and he hands it out to you and just goes, "Please,
take this and never come back. Please."

02:34:41.796 --> 02:34:42.930
TRAVIS: For the rest of the day?

02:34:42.930 --> 02:34:50.475
MATT: "Ever again. Your presence has brought me no
end of pain. Just go."

02:34:50.762 --> 02:34:54.559
TRAVIS: Obviously, we've gotten the better end of
this deal.

02:34:54.559 --> 02:34:58.186
SAM: I think that that is true, absolutely.

02:34:58.186 --> 02:34:59.171
TRAVIS: Do you still have the--

02:34:59.171 --> 02:35:00.322
MATT: "Go!"

02:35:00.322 --> 02:35:01.582
TRAVIS: We should go. We should leave.

02:35:01.582 --> 02:35:04.087
SAM: All right. Thank you for your--

02:35:04.087 --> 02:35:06.921
MATT: (incoherent noises)

02:35:06.921 --> 02:35:10.466
SAM: Good day to you. Let's go. Doty, come.

02:35:10.466 --> 02:35:11.540
TRAVIS: Bidet.

02:35:11.540 --> 02:35:21.200
MATT: Doty turns. "Ahh!" And comes running after
you guys as you exit the shop.

02:35:21.200 --> 02:35:22.379
LIAM: Holy shit.

02:35:22.379 --> 02:35:24.266
TALIESIN: That was amazing. I don't feel good.

02:35:24.266 --> 02:35:26.898
MARISHA: Wow.

02:35:26.898 --> 02:35:30.945
TRAVIS: Good job. We've got to go. We've got to
hole up somewhere for a minute.

02:35:30.945 --> 02:35:32.371
You know. A drink?

02:35:32.371 --> 02:35:33.891
SAM: Please.

02:35:33.891 --> 02:35:36.870
TRAVIS: Yeah. Is there a tavern near this shop?

02:35:36.870 --> 02:35:38.806
MATT: In the Quad Roads? Yeah. There's actually
quite a few taverns.

02:35:38.806 --> 02:35:41.057
SAM: As soon as we step outside, I barf all over
the floor.

02:35:41.057 --> 02:35:42.899
(all laugh)

02:35:42.899 --> 02:35:44.986
TRAVIS: Where was that? What the fuck?

02:35:44.986 --> 02:35:47.735
SAM: I'm sorry. It just comes naturally. I can't
force it.

02:35:47.735 --> 02:35:54.634
