03:01:05.178 --> 03:01:14.351
LIAM: Do you know what I like? I like the version
of you that my sister brings out.

03:01:14.351 --> 03:01:29.100
TALIESIN: I do too. I'll do my best to keep him in
the forefront. And as for you: I like the version

03:01:29.100 --> 03:01:40.544
of you that's not afraid. So let's go meet this
terrible thing, drop off the book, get you feeling

03:01:40.544 --> 03:01:42.809
a bit better.

03:01:42.809 --> 03:01:45.258
LIAM: (clears throat) Come on.

03:01:45.258 --> 03:01:48.036
TALIESIN: Fuck. (clears throat)

03:01:48.036 --> 03:01:55.341
MATT: As you both ascend the stairs, you see
standing-- previously not noticed as you guys were

03:01:55.341 --> 03:02:01.088
having a conversation-- but off to the sides of
each side of the entryway, the two doors that are

03:02:01.088 --> 03:02:07.599
closed, there are two women in long black gowns
with dark veils that drift over their head to the

03:02:07.599 --> 03:02:14.419
mid torso, that you had lead you into the chamber
initially. Both suddenly present themselves, bow,

03:02:14.419 --> 03:02:20.887
and step out of the side as the chamber doors open
to the interior of the Raven's Crest temple.

03:02:20.887 --> 03:02:28.439
There, standing as the doors open, is what looks
to be an older woman wearing the same attire, the

03:02:28.439 --> 03:02:35.126
same dark veil, somewhat able to see her features
beneath the dark material that hangs in front of

03:02:35.126 --> 03:02:39.175
her. She steps forward as the doors open.

03:02:40.764 --> 03:03:00.832
LIAM: Hello there. You recognize me. This is my
friend. We bring you an offering for the Queen.

03:03:04.023 --> 03:03:09.022
MATT: The woman bends down, takes the tome from
your hand. She holds it, she takes her fingers and

03:03:09.022 --> 03:03:17.279
brushes the cloth away that currently obscures the
tome, takes a look at it, holds it a foot further

03:03:17.279 --> 03:03:24.928
away from her face, and throws the cloth over the
front, clasps it in her arms and brings it down

03:03:25.142 --> 03:03:30.183
towards her torso. And, for the first time since
this-- you've heard her speak before, you have

03:03:30.183 --> 03:03:35.387
done this before-- but the strange eerie kind of
airy whisper comes out from this older woman as

03:03:35.387 --> 03:03:47.734
she bends forward, clutching this tome. "We thank
you. And we will be sure that this finds its final seal."

03:03:54.506 --> 03:04:10.429
LIAM: She has begun to speak to me. Her desires
are not clear, entirely, but I am listening. And I

03:04:10.429 --> 03:04:13.218
intend to learn.

03:04:14.870 --> 03:04:16.940
MATT: "Good."

03:04:20.837 --> 03:04:26.449
LIAM: We have to go. But I mean to come back.

03:04:26.630 --> 03:04:34.712
MATT: "Whenever you're ready. The vision of the
gods is obscured beyond the Divine Gate. We are

03:04:34.712 --> 03:04:41.160
"not just their tools but their extensions. The
creations that act as their fingers in this plane.

03:04:41.212 --> 03:04:57.911
"The center of all other life and death. Be
watchful. Be vigilant." She bows, and backs into

03:04:57.911 --> 03:05:03.884
the Raven's Crest once more as the doors close,
the two other women now flanking out of the

03:05:03.884 --> 03:05:07.867
shadows and stepping before each door, and
seemingly just

03:05:07.867 --> 03:05:10.720
not paying attention to your presence.

03:05:12.902 --> 03:05:20.716
TALIESIN: I was envious of you once. God. So
sorry. (sighs)

03:05:20.716 --> 03:05:24.588
LIAM: (whispers) Good day.

03:05:24.588 --> 03:05:26.173
MATT: They make no response as you guys turn and
make your way

03:05:26.173 --> 03:05:28.933
down the stairs from the Raven's Crest.

03:05:32.949 --> 03:05:41.592
TALIESIN: Just so you know, it is your duty to
