mistakes that I may have made. I take full

03:23:22.325 --> 03:23:31.194
responsibility for this, and I throw myself at
your feet for mercy. I know I'm new to this team,

03:23:31.194 --> 03:23:39.607
and I hoped that this gift would be a peacemaking
gesture. By the way, you should divide all these

03:23:39.607 --> 03:23:41.729
potions up as you see fit.

03:23:41.729 --> 03:23:43.740
LAURA: We totally should.

03:23:43.740 --> 03:23:55.789
SAM: And I'm sorry if I made mistakes today. But
we're all alive, we have what we need, and we're

03:23:55.789 --> 03:23:58.976
still on an adventure, right?

03:23:58.976 --> 03:24:02.397
TALIESIN: A toast to mistakes--

03:24:02.397 --> 03:24:04.824
SAM: Let's all sing our fight song, shall we?

03:24:04.824 --> 03:24:07.644
TALIESIN: -- and to terrible consequences, to
failure.

03:24:07.644 --> 03:24:09.292
LAURA: How about you go first, Tary.

03:24:09.292 --> 03:24:11.466
MARISHA: Yes, let's learn it from you.

03:24:11.538 --> 03:24:23.299
SAM: Doty, show me what we wrote. (sings) 'Seven
intrepid warriors we, were strong before and

03:24:23.299 --> 03:24:33.818
'stronger with me. Drinking wine and Heroes'
Feasts, saving maidens, defeating beasts. We

03:24:33.818 --> 03:24:44.071
'fight, fight, fight, with strength and girth, I
slew a marid and proved my worth. Vix and Vox,

03:24:44.071 --> 03:24:58.320
'Kiko and Greg, and Percival with the head like an
egg. I defeated a kraken too, and I saved the

03:24:58.320 --> 03:25:06.799
'Ashari single-handedly in the ocean blue. We
fight, fight, fight, with strength and girth. I

03:25:06.799 --> 03:25:12.368
'won your hearts and I proved my worth.'

03:25:12.368 --> 03:25:14.230
TALIESIN: Ooh. Bravo!

03:25:14.230 --> 03:25:16.639
LAURA: Hey!

03:25:16.639 --> 03:25:19.865
SAM: Now you all have fight songs too, don't you?

03:25:19.865 --> 03:25:22.954
TALIESIN: We'll cover that at the next drink. I
think it's time to turn in.

03:25:22.954 --> 03:25:24.225
MARISHA: Hm, yes.

03:25:24.225 --> 03:25:25.170
LAURA: Wow.

03:25:25.170 --> 03:25:28.263
TALIESIN: I'm going to run-- I'm going to get a
little bit of the hardest alcohol that they have,

03:25:28.263 --> 03:25:32.971
preferably a clear alcohol, and ask them if they
have any chicken, like-- or some sort of meat that

03:25:32.971 --> 03:25:34.733
they're about to throw away.

03:25:34.733 --> 03:25:37.630
LAURA: Oh. Chicken.

03:25:37.630 --> 03:25:38.909
TALIESIN: Stop it.

03:25:38.909 --> 03:25:43.263
MATT: They do have some near-spoiling meat. And at
the cost of one gold piece you can get a pretty

03:25:43.263 --> 03:25:44.374
solid bottle.

03:25:44.374 --> 03:25:51.675
TALIESIN: I pop it and I'm just going to try and
start solventing away the glue with grease, with

03:25:51.675 --> 03:25:54.319
fatty grease and alcohol.

03:25:54.319 --> 03:25:57.273
MATT: It'll take you the better part of the
next couple of hours, but you can do it.

03:25:57.321 --> 03:26:00.931
TALIESIN: Yeah, I'm just going to try and get this
thing off. Let me try and remove the hair too.

03:26:00.931 --> 03:26:05.859
MATT: You do manage to get the hair off. You don't
get all the glue splotches. Doty now has these,

03:26:05.859 --> 03:26:11.962
like, clusters of nasty-looking glue splotches all
over the head. And of like, taken pieces of

03:26:12.016 --> 03:26:18.162
thread, and fuzz, and dirt and things just from
the atmosphere to him. It looks awful. Doty looks

03:26:18.162 --> 03:26:22.115
awful. But the cloak does come off.

03:26:23.253 --> 03:26:24.849
TALIESIN: We'll have it cleaned, dear.

03:26:24.849 --> 03:26:28.782
LAURA: That's amazing. So worth it, darling, I
can't believe you did that. Thank you.

03:26:28.782 --> 03:26:31.317
LIAM: Does the cloak of Elvenkind look like butt?

03:26:31.317 --> 03:26:32.746
LAURA: It's got clumps of red hair stuck.

03:26:32.746 --> 03:26:36.479
MATT: Only like 10% butt. Like, there is still
glue on it. You have to spend more time.

03:26:36.479 --> 03:26:37.437
LIAM: It worked?

03:26:37.437 --> 03:26:38.428
SAM: Did we take off the mask?

03:26:38.428 --> 03:26:39.830
MATT: If you want to.

03:26:39.830 --> 03:26:41.288
TALIESIN: It looks like the kindergarten class
attacked it.

03:26:41.288 --> 03:26:42.002
MARISHA: Yeah.

03:26:42.002 --> 03:26:43.020
SAM: Should we take off the mask?

03:26:43.020 --> 03:26:43.798
LAURA: Probably.

03:26:43.798 --> 03:26:44.443
TALIESIN: Fucker.

03:26:44.443 --> 03:26:45.633
SAM and TALIESIN: There's another one!

03:26:45.633 --> 03:26:47.081
(all laugh)

03:26:47.132 --> 03:26:50.032
MATT: It's like a hydra, Travis killed one, two
more took its place.

03:26:50.032 --> 03:26:51.531
TRAVIS: It's so strange man, they go up, they come
back down.

03:26:51.531 --> 03:26:56.239
TALIESIN: Arsehole, where did you go? Fuck.
They're huge. Sorry. That was really

03:26:56.239 --> 03:26:58.700
inappropriate.

03:26:58.700 --> 03:27:00.727
MATT: So, as you guys get tired, you could rent a
room for the evening.

03:27:00.727 --> 03:27:01.693
LAURA: Yeah.

03:27:01.693 --> 03:27:02.984
MATT: At the tavern if you'd like, the Siren's
Succor.

03:27:02.984 --> 03:27:04.468
LAURA: Okay, let's rent a room.

03:27:04.468 --> 03:27:08.688
MATT: Okay. So, I'd say for the rooms for all of
you guys tonight, drinking there, mark off ten

03:27:08.688 --> 03:27:10.673
gold, it's fine.

03:27:10.673 --> 03:27:12.248
SAM: For everyone, or each.

03:27:12.248 --> 03:27:12.918
LAURA: For everyone.

03:27:12.918 --> 03:27:13.708
MATT: For everyone.

03:27:13.708 --> 03:27:14.672
SAM: Pf.

03:27:14.672 --> 03:27:15.331
TALIESIN: I know.

03:27:15.331 --> 03:27:16.075
TRAVIS: Yeah.

03:27:16.075 --> 03:27:17.593
SAM: I can take care of this, if you'd like.

03:27:17.593 --> 03:27:18.845
TALIESIN: No, we got this. It's okay.

03:27:18.845 --> 03:27:20.424
LAURA: We've got it. It's fine, Tary.

03:27:20.424 --> 03:27:21.542
TALIESIN: But part of being--

03:27:21.542 --> 03:27:26.610
LIAM: You buy the potions, we pay for the shitty
hotel rooms.

03:27:26.610 --> 03:27:31.644
SAM: (laughs) I don't know if that evens out. But
all right.

03:27:31.644 --> 03:27:36.310
TALIESIN: Don't think of it as a thing that evens
out, think of it as an ever-increasing debt that

03:27:36.310 --> 03:27:39.147
doesn't really ever get paid.

03:27:39.147 --> 03:27:40.979
SAM: I like the way you think, science bro.

03:27:40.979 --> 03:27:42.721
TALIESIN: Cheers.

03:27:42.721 --> 03:27:53.242
MATT: All righty. As you guys rest for the
evening, the morning comes around. You're across

03:27:53.242 --> 03:27:57.317
the board, fairly hung-over, but functional.
Except for Grog, Grog, you're fine. Yay

03:27:57.317 --> 03:28:04.945
constitution 20! But you guys muster yourselves,
get a quick bite to eat downstairs, in the now

03:28:04.996 --> 03:28:13.105
even-more-empty tavern. Your dresses are at the
ready, you go and collect them. What's next, what

03:28:13.105 --> 03:28:16.303
do you guys want to do?

03:28:17.121 --> 03:28:19.155
LAURA: We should go to see your people.

03:28:19.155 --> 03:28:20.850
MARISHA: I mean, we could catch brunch first?

03:28:20.850 --> 03:28:23.121
LAURA: No. We should go to see. Your. People.

03:28:23.121 --> 03:28:23.837
TALIESIN: No.

03:28:23.837 --> 03:28:24.420
LIAM: No.

03:28:24.420 --> 03:28:26.520
MARISHA: All right. Yeah, yeah, yeah. Yeah. Yeah.
Let's go.

03:28:26.520 --> 03:28:28.488
LIAM: No time like the present.

03:28:28.488 --> 03:28:31.248
LAURA: Wait, what are the colors of Whitestone
again?

03:28:31.248 --> 03:28:35.098
TALIESIN: Lavender, white, blue, gold, silver.

03:28:35.098 --> 03:28:36.913
LAURA: That's the colors I want my dress to be.

03:28:36.913 --> 03:28:38.052
TRAVIS: That's five.

03:28:38.052 --> 03:28:38.837
MATT: Okay.

03:28:38.841 --> 03:28:40.115
LIAM: It's too late, it's black.

03:28:40.115 --> 03:28:41.851
(all laugh)

03:28:41.851 --> 03:28:46.449
TALIESIN: I might add, you do-- Part of taking a
crest is that you actually do get to build

03:28:46.449 --> 03:28:48.863
something of your own.

03:28:48.863 --> 03:28:50.642
LAURA: We need to work on that, Percival.

03:28:50.642 --> 03:28:56.806
TALIESIN: We do. I was-- I feel like I've been
negligent. That we've not been--

03:28:56.806 --> 03:28:59.680
LAURA: You also need to explain to me what
the fucking Grey Hunt is at some point.

03:28:59.734 --> 03:29:06.683
TALIESIN: Yes, we should get to that. I only
know because we've talked about that.

03:29:06.737 --> 03:29:08.171
MATT: Yeah. All right.

03:29:08.171 --> 03:29:09.788
LAURA: Come on, let's go, Keyleth.

03:29:09.788 --> 03:29:12.418
MARISHA: Okay. Let's go.

03:29:12.418 --> 03:29:14.301
LAURA: Antlers upon antlers.

03:29:14.301 --> 03:29:20.413
MATT: All right. And such. With the Transport Via
Plants spell cast into the nearest tree, you guys

03:29:20.413 --> 03:29:24.416
find yourself emerging from one of the
cliffside trees that have grown out of the

03:29:24.480 --> 03:29:32.345
outcropping of stone and rock that marks the
exterior of Zephra. Did you all travel here last

03:29:32.345 --> 03:29:34.054
time, or was it just Keyleth and Vax?

03:29:34.054 --> 03:29:36.945
MARISHA: It was just Vax and Allura--

03:29:36.945 --> 03:29:38.652
MATT: Yeah, Vax. Allura, that's right.

03:29:38.652 --> 03:29:39.313
TALIESIN: Ooh.

03:29:39.313 --> 03:29:41.078
MARISHA: Whom we kind of forgot was with us.
(nervous laugh)

03:29:41.078 --> 03:29:42.523
MATT: That's right, and she was like, "Whatever."

03:29:42.523 --> 03:29:43.664
MARISHA: Yeah.

03:29:43.664 --> 03:29:49.578
MATT: All right, so you guys all emerge, and you
see now, on these extremely tall mountain bluffs,

03:29:49.578 --> 03:29:57.565
the wind is strong on the outskirts, and you can
see, whizzing past you, puffs of cloud, and leaf,

03:29:57.565 --> 03:30:03.316
and dust. But it's all contained on the outside of
this bluff. And before you on the opposite side,

03:30:03.316 --> 03:30:10.058
built deep into this mountain top, you can see
dozens and dozens of structures made from the

03:30:10.058 --> 03:30:15.416
natural stone and bending of long wood slats that
seem to have been curved over into these dome-like

03:30:15.416 --> 03:30:22.245
structures. You see small trees emerging in
places, and even though you are a few hundred feet

03:30:22.245 --> 03:30:28.991
off, you can already see maybe 20 or so various
people just wandering the town, some of which are

03:30:28.991 --> 03:30:35.437
outside working on-- sitting on benches, working on
various crafts. You can see leathers being dried

03:30:35.502 --> 03:30:42.778
out from various hides. You catch the sight of a
griffin that swoops past and disappears into a

03:30:42.778 --> 03:30:46.664
nearby cloud. And looking over the bluff--

03:30:46.664 --> 03:30:47.438
SAM: Cool.

03:30:47.438 --> 03:30:51.631
MATT: -- about ten feet off, this is the drop, goes
down for hundreds of feet before vanishing into

03:30:51.683 --> 03:30:57.717
low-hanging clouds. You guys have no idea how high
up you are, but it seems very high.

03:30:57.717 --> 03:31:00.865
MARISHA: (inhales) Oh man.

03:31:00.865 --> 03:31:01.955
SAM: Are we falling?

03:31:01.955 --> 03:31:03.210
LAURA: Is it super windy?

03:31:03.210 --> 03:31:04.305
MARISHA: No no no, we're on the mountain.

03:31:04.305 --> 03:31:06.959
MATT: You can see a lot of wind rushing just
around you, but it seems like this portion of the

03:31:06.959 --> 03:31:13.420
mountain is almost protected, or at least the
winds are guided in a way where they're not

03:31:13.420 --> 03:31:16.205
affecting this portion of the mountain.

03:31:17.822 --> 03:31:19.208
LAURA: So what do we do?

03:31:19.208 --> 03:31:20.714
LIAM: What happens now, boss?

03:31:20.714 --> 03:31:26.426
MARISHA: I forgot you guys haven't seen my
hometown yet. Okay, all right. Let's go that way.

03:31:26.426 --> 03:31:31.981
Okay. See, over there is where I caught
my first baby griffin--

03:31:31.981 --> 03:31:33.090
TALIESIN: Oh no.

03:31:33.090 --> 03:31:36.622
MARISHA: -- he was lost and got separated from his
mom, and I captured him up, and I tucked him up under

03:31:36.622 --> 03:31:39.300
my shirt. And over there actually--

03:31:39.300 --> 03:31:40.366
TALIESIN: (groans)

03:31:40.366 --> 03:31:42.756
MARISHA: -- I tripped and fell and that was the
first time that I scraped my knee--

03:31:42.756 --> 03:31:43.770
SAM: Amazing.

03:31:43.770 --> 03:31:45.098
MARISHA: -- and I was like, oh no, I'm bleeding.

03:31:45.098 --> 03:31:46.174
SAM: It must have been terrible.

03:31:46.174 --> 03:31:48.503
LAURA: While she was walking, I go behind and do
this to Vax.

03:31:48.503 --> 03:31:49.363
MARISHA: Oh, it was so terrible, yeah.

03:31:49.363 --> 03:31:49.954
LIAM: Ow.

03:31:49.954 --> 03:31:50.719
LAURA: Does it still hurt?

03:31:50.719 --> 03:31:52.503
LIAM: No it's fine, I feel good. I feel really
good.

03:31:52.503 --> 03:31:53.206
LAURA: Yeah?

03:31:53.206 --> 03:31:59.185
LIAM: Yeah, I feel really good. I feel rested. I
feel fucking healthy man. I don't know. I'm

03:31:59.185 --> 03:32:01.634
serious.

03:32:01.634 --> 03:32:05.179
LAURA: All right, that's happy.

03:32:05.179 --> 03:32:06.375
LIAM: (growls)

03:32:06.375 --> 03:32:07.970
LAURA: (growls)

03:32:07.970 --> 03:32:14.923
MATT: As you guys are walking closer to the
outside of Zephra, you see a couple of individuals

03:32:14.923 --> 03:32:19.328
beginning to approach, three or four children,
just seeing these strange visitors in the

03:32:19.328 --> 03:32:25.232
outskirts. They're also keeping low and not trying
to draw your attention too strongly, though they

03:32:25.232 --> 03:32:30.806
are out in the middle of the open. You see a few
bushes and elements. You see two grown individuals

03:32:30.806 --> 03:32:38.598
walking up with the children, one of which appears
to be a relatively young girl, maybe around 13, 14

03:32:38.598 --> 03:32:44.992
years old who pushes the kids to the back and
goes, "Keyleth?"

03:32:45.427 --> 03:32:49.162
MARISHA: Yes, hi, hi. What's your name?

03:32:49.162 --> 03:32:52.974
MATT: "Sora. You used to watch over me when I was
little."

03:32:52.974 --> 03:32:59.901
MARISHA: Oh my goodness, Sora. Wow, last time I
saw you, you were like, like, oh man. Look how big

03:32:59.901 --> 03:33:01.594
you've gotten.

03:33:01.594 --> 03:33:02.665
MATT: "I--"

03:33:02.665 --> 03:33:07.185
MARISHA: Do you still know that handshake? Do you
remember the--

03:33:07.185 --> 03:33:08.734
MATT: It takes a moment for you guys to figure it
out.

03:33:08.734 --> 03:33:10.590
MARISHA: And there, you've got it. You got it.

03:33:10.590 --> 03:33:12.270
MATT: It's slightly awkward, but for the most part
you recall it.

03:33:12.270 --> 03:33:13.230
MARISHA: Yeah, yeah.

03:33:13.230 --> 03:33:14.402
MATT: "I'm much older now, I don't need to--"

03:33:14.402 --> 03:33:15.074
MARISHA: Oh man.

03:33:15.074 --> 03:33:15.991
MATT: "I didn't--"

03:33:15.991 --> 03:33:16.628
MARISHA: You forgot--

03:33:16.628 --> 03:33:17.627
MATT: "You're back."

03:33:17.627 --> 03:33:21.145
MARISHA: Yeah. I guess I am.

03:33:21.145 --> 03:33:24.268
MATT: "We have to tell everyone else."

03:33:24.268 --> 03:33:25.832
MARISHA: Hey, hey.

03:33:25.832 --> 03:33:29.062
MATT: The kids are all just quietly staring
wide-eyed and smiling quietly.

03:33:29.062 --> 03:33:33.701
MARISHA: Sora, Sora. Have you seen my dad around?

03:33:33.701 --> 03:33:35.572
MATT: "Do you want me to get him?"

03:33:35.572 --> 03:33:36.316
MARISHA: Yeah.

03:33:36.316 --> 03:33:36.990
MATT: "Okay."

03:33:36.990 --> 03:33:37.752
MARISHA: Okay.

03:33:37.752 --> 03:33:40.613
MATT: "C'mon, c'mon kids." And takes them by the
hand and they all drag the kids off as you guys

03:33:40.613 --> 03:33:44.524
wait in the outskirts of the city. One of the kids
who didn't quite get a hand on this young

03:33:44.524 --> 03:33:49.330
three-year-old boy who's running behind them
stops. Turns and stares at you all, but stares

03:33:49.330 --> 03:33:53.775
specifically at Grog and is just wide-eyed,
going--

03:33:54.300 --> 03:33:55.793
TRAVIS: Hey.

03:33:55.793 --> 03:33:59.224
MATT: "Hi."

03:33:59.481 --> 03:34:02.502
TRAVIS: Eat your vegetables, you'll look like
this.

03:34:02.502 --> 03:34:06.275
MATT: "Okay."

03:34:06.275 --> 03:34:07.233
TRAVIS: Now get out of here!

03:34:07.233 --> 03:34:08.176
MATT: (yells)

03:34:08.176 --> 03:34:09.402
(all laugh)

03:34:09.402 --> 03:34:12.336
MATT: Just immediately bolts past to catch up with
the rest of the crowd.

03:34:12.336 --> 03:34:16.324
TALIESIN: So I believe you just set up a lifetime
of unreasonable expectations.

03:34:16.324 --> 03:34:17.915
TRAVIS: He'll be healthy, though.

03:34:17.915 --> 03:34:19.756
LAURA: I've never seen Grog eat a single
vegetable--

03:34:19.756 --> 03:34:20.751
TRAVIS: No, fuck those things.

03:34:20.751 --> 03:34:22.608
LAURA: -- the entire time I've known him.

03:34:22.608 --> 03:34:23.740
TALIESIN: I was wondering about that.

03:34:23.740 --> 03:34:26.029
TRAVIS: Nothing in green is good.

03:34:27.080 --> 03:34:32.372
MATT: A short time passes. A few moments, before
you begin to see the city suddenly come to more

03:34:32.372 --> 03:34:37.176
vibrant life. People are stepping out of their
abodes. Dozens of individuals are beginning to

03:34:37.176 --> 03:34:41.400
come together, talking, whispering, and some
looking back and watching you all in the outskirts

03:34:41.400 --> 03:34:45.957
of Zephra, until eventually it seems a procession
of some kind is all gathering and moving out of

03:34:45.957 --> 03:34:52.122
this mass of people in your direction. As you
look, you begin to see people adorned in similar

03:34:52.122 --> 03:34:57.688
clothing as to when you first encountered Keyleth
in the swamps outside of Stillben. You see these

03:34:57.688 --> 03:35:05.466
leather-based, almost scaled-looking armor that
drifts down to the legs. You see people that hold

03:35:05.466 --> 03:35:15.726
giant staffs that hold golds and greens and blue
colors that mark the symbols of the Zephra tribe.

03:35:15.726 --> 03:35:23.966
And then, in the center of them, you've met once
before, you see stepping forth, Korren, the father

03:35:23.966 --> 03:35:31.638
of Keyleth and the current acting Voice of Tempest
of the Zephra. His long white, silver hair

03:35:31.638 --> 03:35:37.782
drifting behind him. He approaches with a look.
Everyone holds back as he steps forth from the

03:35:37.782 --> 03:35:43.773
crowd and ignoring the rest of you, just goes and
beelines straight to Keyleth. You can see him, he

03:35:43.839 --> 03:35:50.368
has a bit of a limp to him that you don't recall
from last time, but he seems other than that in

03:35:50.368 --> 03:35:56.156
good health. As he approaches you, he clasps his
hands out in front of him and takes a good long

03:35:56.156 --> 03:36:01.535
look at you as he reaches out and takes your hands
into his own. "My daughter."

03:36:01.575 --> 03:36:06.129
MARISHA: I just drop to a knee and say, Kaitiyaki,
father.

03:36:06.129 --> 03:36:16.881
MATT: "Kaitiyaki, Keyleth. We've heard that the
defense of Emon was successful, yes?"

03:36:17.389 --> 03:36:26.071
MARISHA: Yes, we have defeated the Chroma
Conclave. The help of Vox Machina and many many

03:36:26.071 --> 03:36:28.883
others, at the cost of many lives.

03:36:28.883 --> 03:36:33.354
MATT: "Good, good. I'm glad we could be of some
aid to your journey."

03:36:33.426 --> 03:36:40.199
MARISHA: Yes, thank you. The Air Ashari were very
valuable during that day. Very courageous.

03:36:40.203 --> 03:36:46.723
MATT: "And we will remember those we lost in that
fray. The great sacrifices that they gave so that

03:36:46.723 --> 03:36:55.052
"these children could live. So?" And at this point,
he now takes notice of the rest of the group. "By

03:36:55.214 --> 03:37:03.685
"what joy do we have of bringing your allies here
and returning to your people?"

03:37:03.975 --> 03:37:06.052
LAURA: He doesn't know.

03:37:06.052 --> 03:37:18.108
MARISHA: Sorry, I thought Uvenda might have said
something. I'm here because I have completed my

03:37:18.108 --> 03:37:21.346
Aramente, and have come for my blessing.

03:37:21.520 --> 03:37:22.451
MATT: "Yes, you have."

03:37:22.451 --> 03:37:24.542
LAURA: (gasps)

03:37:25.162 --> 03:37:28.276
MATT: "I just wanted to hear it from your lips."

03:37:30.143 --> 03:37:37.157
MARISHA: Still waiting on your final word, I
guess.

03:37:37.383 --> 03:37:48.354
MATT: "Well, while we still have daylight, let us
prepare for the ceremony. Come, come, all of you.

03:37:48.354 --> 03:37:59.216
"You are welcome, welcome here in Zephra. We'll
begin, decoration shall commence. Rest, prepare,

03:37:59.439 --> 03:38:04.524
"naught but two or three hours until the ceremony
is to occur." He turns, and folks begin to rush

03:38:04.524 --> 03:38:10.417
in, and people just begin to barrage you with
questions and congratulations, and a number of

03:38:10.417 --> 03:38:14.605
individuals who seem to have heard stories, many
second-hand, and exaggerations of the various

03:38:14.605 --> 03:38:21.517
things that you've accomplished over the past year
or so here in Tal'Dorei. You answer questions, you

03:38:21.517 --> 03:38:26.695
play into the tall tales if you want. One child
turns to you and goes, "And who are you?"

03:38:27.241 --> 03:38:28.662
SAM: Taryon Darrington.

03:38:28.662 --> 03:38:29.945
MATT: "I don't know who you are."

03:38:29.945 --> 03:38:30.669
SAM: You will.

03:38:30.669 --> 03:38:31.415
MATT: "You--"

03:38:31.415 --> 03:38:33.652
(all laugh)

03:38:33.652 --> 03:38:42.044
MATT: There is a massive interest around Grog as
goliaths generally do not travel this far up into

03:38:42.044 --> 03:38:46.385
the territory of the mountain. Most of them stay
far north in the Cliffkeep or wandering the

03:38:46.385 --> 03:38:52.832
dividing plain. They're just swarming you and
climbing up on you and hanging from your arms and

03:38:53.054 --> 03:38:57.324
you feel kind of awkward but kind of enjoying the
attention at the same time.

03:38:57.324 --> 03:38:59.194
TRAVIS: They're really little.

03:38:59.194 --> 03:39:00.915
LAURA: Kind of like gnomes.

03:39:00.915 --> 03:39:02.170
TRAVIS: Yeah. (gasps)

03:39:02.170 --> 03:39:04.069
(all laugh)

03:39:04.069 --> 03:39:05.910
TALIESIN: Well that works, well done.

03:39:05.910 --> 03:39:07.445
TRAVIS: I'm good.

03:39:07.445 --> 03:39:15.726
MATT: Immediately, over the next hour or two,
people begin to gather floral wreaths and strips

03:39:15.726 --> 03:39:20.988
of silk and material that have been prepared
specifically for these types of occasions. Many of

03:39:21.145 --> 03:39:26.131
them new, made from the recent generations in
preparation, many that are held over by tradition

03:39:26.182 --> 03:39:33.030
and by the various leaders that came before you.
Many that may have had the hope of the return of

03:39:33.030 --> 03:39:38.463
Vilya, but instead, carry through with memory of
Keyleth. As this transpires, you guys are brought

03:39:38.463 --> 03:39:47.024
food, you are gathered into a central open
celebration. Almost like a pit that descends about

03:39:47.024 --> 03:39:52.214
two feet, and there are a number of stools and
tables, and food and drink are brought about. As

03:39:52.214 --> 03:39:57.616
opposed to an event and then a celebration
afterward, it seems to be a reverse here at

03:39:57.616 --> 03:40:03.971
Zephra. It's a build-up. It's everyone, the
excitement grows. As this is happening, you glance

03:40:04.026 --> 03:40:10.669
off and there is one very large, singular tree
right across the way, at the very edge of the

03:40:10.669 --> 03:40:16.848
precipice of this rocky outcropping that holds
most of the city of Zephra. And there at the edge

03:40:16.848 --> 03:40:24.801
you see one large, twisting, gnarled tree that
curves upward. Not quite Sun Tree in height and

03:40:24.801 --> 03:40:30.527
size, but still very elegant and beautiful with
long, thin branches that gently sway on the

03:40:30.527 --> 03:40:35.748
outskirts of whatever barrier seems to bend and
twist the winds from coming and scattering the

03:40:35.748 --> 03:40:42.504
village. You watch as people step up to it, and
they're leaving jewelry, they're putting large

03:40:42.504 --> 03:40:47.229
ribbons across it. Elements of it remind you of
the tree that was in the center of the temple in

03:40:47.229 --> 03:40:55.956
Vesrah, though a different texture. It seems to be
a deep, vibrant, healthy dark brown, and with

03:40:55.956 --> 03:41:03.558
elements of gray bark, with moss that grow at the
base and tuck under the branches, where the

03:41:03.558 --> 03:41:11.086
shadows tend to linger throughout the day.
Eventually, it seems that they have returned and

03:41:11.086 --> 03:41:19.848
the decor is set, benches have been moved, and
most of the people of Zephra are now shifting in

03:41:19.848 --> 03:41:21.744
the direction of this tree.

03:41:21.744 --> 03:41:26.406
LIAM: In all the hubbub and the movement, a few
moments before, I've been watching for Korren, and

03:41:26.406 --> 03:41:30.492
when I see him alone for a second, I make a
beeline toward him.

03:41:30.492 --> 03:41:34.633
MATT: He's in the process of a conversation. And
it's interesting. During this whole thing, he was

03:41:34.633 --> 03:41:40.171
excited to see you and that you've come, but he's
also-- he's kept a strange distance from you

03:41:40.171 --> 03:41:49.454
during this preparation. He smiles, and you guys
meet eyes occasionally, but he's also just

03:41:49.454 --> 03:41:55.977
focusing on this endeavor, and then you kind of
come out of the blue. "Ah, yes, Vax'ildan."

03:41:56.028 --> 03:42:00.119
LIAM: Forgive me. Might I have just a moment?

03:42:00.119 --> 03:42:03.369
MATT: "Quickly. We're about to begin, but yes."

03:42:03.369 --> 03:42:12.132
LIAM: I will be brief. I just wanted to take a
moment to say, I really wish you could've seen

03:42:12.132 --> 03:42:26.896
some of the things she has done. I know you are
proud of her. I've never met anyone like her.

03:42:26.896 --> 03:42:36.313
She's going to do your people very proud. I'm
grateful.

03:42:36.366 --> 03:42:38.845
MATT: "As are we all."

03:42:41.302 --> 03:42:43.324
LIAM: You've a lot to do.

03:42:43.683 --> 03:42:51.074
MATT: "As do you. As does she." And he reaches out
and pats you on the head and ruffles your hair a

03:42:51.074 --> 03:42:57.476
little bit. And even that feels a little awkward
for him, like he felt impulsive to do it, and then

03:42:57.476 --> 03:43:01.923
'oh, that wasn't very-- mm.'

03:43:01.923 --> 03:43:05.385
LIAM: It's all right. It's more than I ever got.

03:43:06.107 --> 03:43:10.578
TALIESIN: Whoa. Ow.

03:43:10.578 --> 03:43:12.240
SAM: Darkness.

03:43:12.240 --> 03:43:21.798
MATT: "Anyway. Come. It's nearly time." And as all
of you are led over, there are spaces at the very

03:43:21.805 --> 03:43:27.431
front of the ceremony, in the semicircle around
this tree. There are platforms set up at the base

03:43:27.431 --> 03:43:37.901
of this tree now. Amongst these hundreds of
various, dangling threads, these small pieces of

03:43:37.901 --> 03:43:42.698
paper that flitter on the outskirts of the gentle
wind that pushes through. You guess they might

03:43:42.698 --> 03:43:48.275
contain wishes or passages or something, but you
see bits of script written on them amongst the

03:43:48.325 --> 03:43:55.369
various glinting pieces of glass and gems and
stone that have been polished. It's small, but beautiful.

03:44:00.065 --> 03:44:07.789
Eventually, you're led to sit in the center of this
semi-circle, and as everyone gathers and takes

03:44:07.962 --> 03:44:12.125
their seat, you hear the occasional kid crying
and people muttering to themself, and eventually

03:44:12.125 --> 03:44:20.974
everyone shushes as Korren, now wearing a very old
ceremonial long light blue and white robe

03:44:20.974 --> 03:44:31.524
wearing what looks to be some sort of a somewhat
tattered, like a scarf that's wrapped around his

03:44:31.524 --> 03:44:35.349
neck and drapes off each of his arms. It's thick and
it's long and it almost touches the ground around

03:44:35.349 --> 03:44:42.763
him, but you can tell from the way he holds it, and 
his arms consistently rest at this crooked position

03:44:42.763 --> 03:44:52.162
that it has some symbolism to this ceremony. As
he steps up under the tree and turns around

03:44:52.162 --> 03:44:58.734
everyone gets very quiet, and the wind seems
to almost stop on the outside of this barrier.

03:44:58.786 --> 03:45:07.624
The rushing, perpetual gust of air
seems to almost hold its breath for this. He

03:45:07.624 --> 03:45:18.008
clears his throat. And as he looks up to everyone,
you swear this tree begins to slowly produce

03:45:18.008 --> 03:45:30.283
cherry blossoms as his words continue. "For long,
we of the winds have awaited the procession of our

03:45:30.283 --> 03:45:39.737
"tradition. With the passing of our elder voice,
Dwala, it was my wife Vilya who was selected to

03:45:39.737 --> 03:45:48.797
"take the Aramente. Beautiful and full of
determination, she accepted her path. And while

03:45:48.797 --> 03:45:57.968
"she did not return to us, the destiny she set is
now seen as one of preparation. Her journey was

03:45:57.968 --> 03:46:09.113
"not in vain, for it was her love that produced our
daughter. It was her guidance in joy that taught

03:46:09.113 --> 03:46:19.320
"our child compassion. It was her discipline and
understanding that forged young Keyleth's spark of

03:46:19.320 --> 03:46:31.563
"intuition and unlocked her adept connection with
nature and the winds. We mourn the loss of our

03:46:31.563 --> 03:46:42.223
"Vilya, but take pride that she lives on in the
eyes of our own, returned, beloved woman of the

03:46:42.223 --> 03:46:51.596
"winds. Here we bring together our collective
voices to bless upon my daughter, the memory of

03:46:51.596 --> 03:47:02.285
"Vilya, the champion of Guasar, the mantle of our
destiny." And as he puts his arms up, from around

03:47:02.285 --> 03:47:08.483
you to each side, Keyleth, you watch as young
acolytes begin to approach from each side, arms

03:47:08.483 --> 03:47:17.464
down. All seemingly carrying these various pieces
of dark green, leather-like material. And as they

03:47:17.464 --> 03:47:27.744
come together, they latch them into place and
slowly build this mantle. "Ring clear our voices

03:47:27.911 --> 03:47:35.520
"to unite our breath and grant our strength to her
guidance and wisdom, as Keyleth takes the rightful

03:47:35.520 --> 03:47:44.010
"and earned responsibility of leading our people
into this next generation." At this point, the

03:47:44.010 --> 03:47:51.849
assembled mantle is placed into Korren's arms. And
you now see this beautiful neck and shoulder piece

03:47:51.849 --> 03:48:01.992
that rests past to the elbows, but limp and without
body, in his hands. As he holds it there and the

03:48:02.053 --> 03:48:06.352
rest of the acolytes step back and find their
place, seated, he lifts his arms up a bit and

03:48:06.352 --> 03:48:20.033
begins to just sing a singular note (sings). And
everyone around you in Zephra begins to join in in

03:48:20.033 --> 03:48:24.352
this singular note. Do you choose to join in as
well?

03:48:24.352 --> 03:48:25.035
TRAVIS: Yeah.

03:48:25.035 --> 03:48:26.311
LAURA: Sure.

03:48:26.311 --> 03:48:32.098
MATT: As you do, the notes begin to separate and
harmonize instinctually. It creates this symphony,

03:48:32.098 --> 03:48:39.915
this beautiful tangling of hundreds of voices from
all across the spectrum. And what at first may

03:48:39.915 --> 03:48:49.947
seem to resemble a discordant hymn, finds this
perfect spread of every note you've ever heard,

03:48:49.947 --> 03:48:59.418
musically merging as one. As he does this,
instinctually, Keyleth, without even thinking, you

03:48:59.418 --> 03:49:07.959
rise and begin to walk towards him. Like the
spirits of generations before you are lifting you

03:49:07.959 --> 03:49:13.592
by your shoulders and elbows, and bring you up
before your father. You find the breath leave your

03:49:13.592 --> 03:49:16.521
lungs, the inside of your mouth is dry.

03:49:16.521 --> 03:49:17.615
MARISHA: Yeah.

03:49:17.615 --> 03:49:21.874
MATT: You're unable to understand what it is
that's driving you, but before you know it you're

03:49:21.874 --> 03:49:27.810
standing before your father, looking up into his
eyes as all of these voices just swirl around you,

03:49:27.810 --> 03:49:33.733
this weird warmth. The nerves in your stomach
still climb to the top and vibrate within your

03:49:33.733 --> 03:49:41.927
chest. As your father places this mantle over your
head and shoulders, and it comes to rest on you,

03:49:41.927 --> 03:49:54.131
heavier than you expected, but it fits well. As he
places this, the green fades to a golden brown and

03:49:54.131 --> 03:50:05.026
red and orange and yellow. And the green leaves
almost drip back into a long, springing trail of a

03:50:05.026 --> 03:50:13.506
cloak behind you that seems to grow with each
passing surge of these voices around her, until it

03:50:13.506 --> 03:50:24.150
reaches the ground and curls behind.
Eventually the cloak stops. The voices soften, and

03:50:24.212 --> 03:50:33.441
come to silence, as you look up once more into
your father's face. "Rise, my daughter, and become

03:50:33.441 --> 03:50:47.446
"Keyleth, Voice of the Tempest." He steps back and
bows his head. Steps off the platform. And you

03:50:47.446 --> 03:50:55.844
stand and turn, and it's just you at the base of
tree, looking about at all of Zephra before you,

03:50:55.844 --> 03:51:01.439
quiet, silent. And your friends before you, at the
front of the crowd.

03:51:12.119 --> 03:51:25.059
MARISHA: Didn't think I'd make it here. I couldn't
have done any of this without not only the support

03:51:25.059 --> 03:51:46.690
of every person in Zephra, and every person of the
Ashari tribe, members of Emon, Tal'Dorei, Marquet,

03:51:46.690 --> 03:52:06.740
even Wildmount. In my journeys, I've learned being
a leader is a global effort, one that takes the

03:52:06.740 --> 03:52:20.818
wisdom of many. Most importantly, I couldn't have
done any of this without Vox Machina. And the

03:52:20.818 --> 03:52:29.972
pieces of them that I've taken away and have
desperately tried to emulate in each one of them

03:52:29.972 --> 03:52:43.519
over the years. Each one of them with qualities
that I admire and strive to embrace. Grog, with

03:52:43.519 --> 03:53:02.930
his strength and his unyielding loyalty. Vex, with
her self-confidence and utter fearlessness. Vax is

03:53:02.930 --> 03:53:13.389
one of the most compassionate people I think I've
ever come across and one of the most brave, even

03:53:13.389 --> 03:53:31.060
if it's maybe foolish. Percival, with your
intelligence and your sensibility, is always there

03:53:31.060 --> 03:53:46.126
to be my balance. Scanlan, with his charisma and
his wit. Pike--

03:53:46.126 --> 03:53:50.999
MATT: As you glance past the group, you can see
just the faint flutter of golden light and energy.

03:53:50.999 --> 03:53:53.975
Wherever she is, a part of her is watching.

03:53:53.975 --> 03:54:08.064
MARISHA: Pike, her generosity and her
authenticity, always true to herself. And even

03:54:08.064 --> 03:54:21.406
Tary. Taryon Darrington, whose blind faith in Vox
Machina and perseverance, trusted us even though

03:54:21.406 --> 03:54:25.045
he probably shouldn't have.

03:54:26.915 --> 03:54:29.488
SAM: (whispers) You're incredible.

03:54:35.343 --> 03:54:44.992
MARISHA: All of these things that I learned and
couldn't be a leader without. Vox Machina makes up

03:54:45.053 --> 03:55:15.098
me. Zephra makes up me. The Ashari people, and all
of greater Exandria. I don't know if I'm the

03:55:15.098 --> 03:55:28.000
leader that you deserve, or a good leader, but I'm
willing to dedicate the rest of my life to doing

03:55:28.000 --> 03:55:37.717
whatever I can for all of us. As long as Vox
Machina stands by my side.

03:55:43.099 --> 03:55:50.565
MATT: At this point, you watch as the light that
remains of the eventually soon-to-come setting sun

03:55:50.565 --> 03:55:56.277
glints across the cheek of Keyleth, the bit of
damp tear that has rolled down her cheek just

03:55:56.277 --> 03:56:03.198
detaches from the edge of her chin and hits the
bottom of the stone. Every cherry blossom in the

03:56:03.198 --> 03:56:11.250
tree releases, and drifts past her from behind,
before getting caught up in the wind just past

03:56:11.250 --> 03:56:21.826
her, causing this swirl of pinks and reds and
whites behind her. Everyone around rises up, and

03:56:21.826 --> 03:56:29.202
they all begin to cheer and clap. All together.
You look around and watch the rest of these

03:56:29.202 --> 03:56:37.374
blossoms slowly drift. You look and see your
friends around you. You look around and you see

03:56:37.374 --> 03:56:43.693
your mother, out of the corner of your eye, just
the memory of her. You sense that if she could be

03:56:43.693 --> 03:56:54.798
here, she would've been. Your father steps up and
takes your hands and just says, "I'm so proud of

03:56:54.798 --> 03:57:06.179
"you. And there's much to be done, I know, but I'm
proud of you." And he takes your hand, and holds

03:57:06.179 --> 03:57:15.504
it up once more. "To the Voice of the Tempest. And
the future of our people." Everyone cheers once

03:57:15.504 --> 03:57:16.546
more together.

03:57:16.546 --> 03:57:17.930
SAM: To Vox Tempesta!

03:57:17.930 --> 03:57:21.516
(all laugh)

03:57:21.809 --> 03:57:25.014
MATT: And with that, you gain the Inspiring Leader
feat.

03:57:25.014 --> 03:57:26.520
MARISHA: What? I get the what now?

03:57:26.520 --> 03:57:30.701
MATT: Inspiring Leader feat, as the end of your
Aramente.

03:57:30.701 --> 03:57:34.185
TRAVIS: Oh, shit, Voice of the Tempest!

03:57:36.223 --> 03:57:41.881
MATT: Which is pretty fun. What that allows you to
do is--

03:57:41.881 --> 03:57:43.820
TRAVIS: You can never die.

03:57:43.820 --> 03:57:52.058
MATT: No, you can totally die. You can spend ten
minutes inspiring your companions, shoring up

03:57:52.058 --> 03:57:57.156
their resolve to fight. When you do so, choose up
to six friendly creatures, which can include

03:57:57.156 --> 03:58:01.028
yourself, within 30 feet that can hear and
understand you. Each creature can gain temporary

03:58:01.028 --> 03:58:04.051
hit points equal to your level plus your charisma
modifier.

03:58:04.244 --> 03:58:07.991
MARISHA: Oh, what! Well, you guys are out of luck
with the charisma modifier shit, but what!

03:58:07.991 --> 03:58:09.842
(all laugh)

03:58:09.842 --> 03:58:13.267
MATT: And they can only gain the temporary hit
points from this until they finish a short or long

03:58:13.267 --> 03:58:17.370
rest. So every short rest you can give everyone 17
temporary hit points.

03:58:17.370 --> 03:58:22.061
MARISHA: That is fucking dope!

03:58:22.127 --> 03:58:23.865
SAM: You have to give a speech every time.

03:58:24.324 --> 03:58:27.388
MATT: Essentially, you take ten minutes to talk
everybody up. So start practicing.

03:58:27.388 --> 03:58:28.988
MARISHA: Jeez, no.

03:58:32.674 --> 03:58:34.248
MATT: And we'll leave it there for the evening.

03:58:34.307 --> 03:58:36.108
LAURA: Oh, man.

03:58:36.108 --> 03:58:38.645
TRAVIS: That was gorgeous, man. That was
gorgeous.

03:58:38.645 --> 03:58:40.264
LAURA: With the tree, man.

03:58:40.264 --> 03:58:46.315
MATT: That was awesome. Completed your Aramente,
took up the mantle, and, apparently, going to the

03:58:46.315 --> 03:58:49.648
Iron City of Dis soon. That's going to be fun.

03:58:50.318 --> 03:58:51.933
TRAVIS: (sings) We built this-- No, no more.

03:58:51.933 --> 03:58:54.034
LAURA: No more of Dis City.

03:58:54.912 --> 03:58:58.898
TALIESIN: I came up with great formal wear for
you, too. It's a shame we didn't get a chance. I

03:58:58.898 --> 03:59:02.128
figured you out.

03:59:02.128 --> 03:59:03.092
TRAVIS: We'll see.

03:59:03.092 --> 03:59:03.850
TALIESIN: All right.

03:59:03.850 --> 03:59:05.042
TRAVIS: Grog has a very discerning taste.

03:59:05.042 --> 03:59:06.742
TALIESIN: I'm very proud I came up with an idea.

03:59:06.742 --> 03:59:09.785
LAURA: Well, I'm glad we went with the blue dress
after that cape turned all the other colors of

03:59:09.785 --> 03:59:11.908
nature and it's like, you are covered.

03:59:11.908 --> 03:59:13.558
MARISHA: Yes.

03:59:13.558 --> 03:59:16.988
(all laugh)

03:59:16.988 --> 03:59:22.109
TRAVIS: Covered, girl.

03:59:22.109 --> 03:59:26.185
MATT: Well done, guys. Thank you again, Loot Crate,
for being our awesome sponsor.

03:59:26.237 --> 03:59:27.723
ALL: Loot Crate!

03:59:27.723 --> 03:59:29.689
TRAVIS: Matt, you did a great job.

03:59:29.689 --> 03:59:33.721
MATT: You guys are always such an absolute
pleasure. Thank you for playing in my weird

03:59:33.721 --> 03:59:35.880
make-up world.

03:59:37.581 --> 03:59:40.873
TALIESIN: How long have you been working on that
